              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2">Etadanik Mistmorgue</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/01/2003&nbsp;: 03:27:43 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Ideally, solo, small-group, and duo exp should all be "relatively" the same, by which I use the term relatively loosely.  Basically, if a soloer is fighting what he is supposed to (generally non-summoning, snareable mobs in PoP and relatively low-hitting mobs outside of PoP), he should be getting exp as well as a group fighting what they're supposed to (slightly tougher mobs in PoP, generally hard-hitting mobs outside of PoP).  However, this should only apply to the true soloing classes - those classes who have always been able to solo well and who compensate for that in being generally weaker in groups/raids.<br /><br />The true bonus to groups should come when they are challenging themselves to new heights - fighting mobs that are way and above the norm of grouping, ie mobs that hit very hard, are impossible to solo, and difficult for even a group to stand against.  Or indoor dungeon zones that are difficult to break, lots of adds, casters, and annoying little quirks like gaters.  Cazic Thule is an excellent example of a place where groups should exceed a soloer's exp.  As might the deeper corners of the Crypt of Decay.  Both zones feature mobs that are immensely strong and who come in numbers - a hefty challenge for the average group, and almost impossible for the average soloer to do consistently, and as such, a perfect candidate for increased group exp.<br /><br />Basically, the group should only be rewarded above the soloer for fighting mobs the soloer cannot, but should be making the same kind of exp for fighting mobs the soloer can also do.  By group, I refer to both the 4-6 man group and the 2-3 man smaller groups.  Neither should take a penalty, with the 2-3 man groups getting better exp overall compared to the 4-6 man groups when they're fighting the same things a soloer is, but being pressed harder also to fight the truly rewarding mobs that a 4-6 man group will do for the best exp.<br /><br />Groups have more options as to what to fight.  They always did.  I'd like to see that preserved based on its original intentions - that groups, being cooperative enterprises, are formed on the basis of taking down bigger, harder, and more difficult mobs - and being rewarded for doing so.  At the same time, I'd like to see soloing also preserved as something unique that only certain classes can do very well - ie as well as groups - though I am not opposed to the idea of giving every class some basic ability to solo while looking for a group.<br /><br />This would be, of course, ideal.<br /></span></font></td>
              </tr>
